---
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import '../../styles/main.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Two-D Visualizations - Chapter 1 | Hacker1 v1.0</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Chapter 1: Data as Revelation - Foundation principles of D3.js visualizations and meaningful data representation." />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}favicon.svg`} />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Century+Schoolbook&family=Roboto:wght@400;500&family=EB+Garamond:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body class="dark-mode two-d-background">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`}>Home</a> → 
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work`}>Finished Work</a> → 
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/two-d`}>Two-D</a> → 
        Chapter 1
      </nav>
      
      <h1>Two-D Visualizations - Chapter 1: Data as Revelation</h1>
      
      <div class="content-section implementation-background">
        <h2>The Divine Order in Data</h2>
        <p>
          "For since the creation of the world God's invisible qualities—his eternal power and divine nature—have been clearly seen, being understood from what has been made." - Romans 1:20
        </p>
        <p>
          Data visualization is the modern art of revealing hidden patterns and divine order 
          within information. Through D3.js and mathematical representation, we transform 
          raw data into meaningful insights that reflect the logical beauty of creation.
        </p>
        
        <blockquote class="highlight">
          "The heavens declare the glory of God; the skies proclaim the work of his hands." - Psalm 19:1
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section solution-background">
        <h2>D3.js as Digital Canvas</h2>
        <p>
          Just as Michelangelo saw David within the marble, we use D3.js to reveal the 
          stories hidden within datasets. Each visualization is both functional analysis 
          and artistic expression, combining technical precision with aesthetic beauty.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Core Visualization Principles:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Clarity over complexity in design</li>
          <li>Truthful representation of data relationships</li>
          <li>Interactive exploration enabling discovery</li>
          <li>Aesthetic beauty serving functional purpose</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Featured Visualization Types:</h3>
        <div class="viz-showcase">
          <div class="viz-item">
            <div class="viz-demo">
              <svg width="200" height="150" viewBox="0 0 200 150">
                <!-- Bar Chart Demo -->
                <rect x="20" y="70" width="15" height="60" fill="#D4AF37" opacity="0.8"/>
                <rect x="40" y="50" width="15" height="80" fill="#8A5A5A" opacity="0.8"/>
                <rect x="60" y="40" width="15" height="90" fill="#5A7A5A" opacity="0.8"/>
                <rect x="80" y="60" width="15" height="70" fill="#7A5A7A" opacity="0.8"/>
                <rect x="100" y="30" width="15" height="100" fill="#D4AF37" opacity="0.8"/>
                <rect x="120" y="80" width="15" height="50" fill="#8A5A5A" opacity="0.8"/>
                <rect x="140" y="45" width="15" height="85" fill="#5A7A5A" opacity="0.8"/>
                <text x="100" y="145" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f0f0f0" font-size="12">Scripture Reading Patterns</text>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4>Bar Charts</h4>
            <p>Comparing categorical data with clarity and visual hierarchy.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="viz-item">
            <div class="viz-demo">
              <svg width="200" height="150" viewBox="0 0 200 150">
                <!-- Line Chart Demo -->
                <polyline points="20,100 40,80 60,70 80,85 100,60 120,75 140,50 160,65 180,45" 
                         fill="none" stroke="#D4AF37" stroke-width="3" opacity="0.8"/>
                <circle cx="20" cy="100" r="3" fill="#D4AF37"/>
                <circle cx="40" cy="80" r="3" fill="#D4AF37"/>
                <circle cx="60" cy="70" r="3" fill="#D4AF37"/>
                <circle cx="80" cy="85" r="3" fill="#D4AF37"/>
                <circle cx="100" cy="60" r="3" fill="#D4AF37"/>
                <circle cx="120" cy="75" r="3" fill="#D4AF37"/>
                <circle cx="140" cy="50" r="3" fill="#D4AF37"/>
                <circle cx="160" cy="65" r="3" fill="#D4AF37"/>
                <circle cx="180" cy="45" r="3" fill="#D4AF37"/>
                <text x="100" y="130" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f0f0f0" font-size="12">Spiritual Growth Timeline</text>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4>Line Charts</h4>
            <p>Tracking change over time with graceful curves and meaningful trends.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="viz-item">
            <div class="viz-demo">
              <svg width="200" height="150" viewBox="0 0 200 150">
                <!-- Scatter Plot Demo -->
                <circle cx="40" cy="80" r="4" fill="#D4AF37" opacity="0.7"/>
                <circle cx="60" cy="60" r="6" fill="#8A5A5A" opacity="0.7"/>
                <circle cx="80" cy="70" r="5" fill="#5A7A5A" opacity="0.7"/>
                <circle cx="100" cy="50" r="7" fill="#7A5A7A" opacity="0.7"/>
                <circle cx="120" cy="65" r="4" fill="#D4AF37" opacity="0.7"/>
                <circle cx="140" cy="45" r="6" fill="#8A5A5A" opacity="0.7"/>
                <circle cx="160" cy="75" r="5" fill="#5A7A5A" opacity="0.7"/>
                <text x="100" y="130" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f0f0f0" font-size="12">Prayer vs. Peace Correlation</text>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4>Scatter Plots</h4>
            <p>Revealing relationships and correlations between spiritual practices.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section experimental-background">
        <h2>Interactive Storytelling</h2>
        <p>
          Like the parables of Jesus, effective data visualization tells stories that 
          reveal deeper truths. Interactive elements allow users to explore data 
          personally, discovering insights through guided investigation.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Interaction Design Principles:</h3>
        <div class="interaction-principles">
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h4>Progressive Disclosure</h4>
            <p>Start with overview, then provide details on demand - like scripture study moving from general themes to specific verses.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h4>Contextual Guidance</h4>
            <p>Provide helpful hints and explanations, guiding users like a shepherd leads his flock.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-item">
            <h4>Meaningful Animation</h4>
            <p>Use transitions that enhance understanding, not distract - smooth and purposeful like divine orchestration.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="navigation-section">
        <div class="nav-buttons">
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/graphic-ch1`} class="button is-light">← Previous: Graphic Chapter 1</a>
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/three-d-ch1`} class="button is-primary">Next: Three-D Chapter 1 →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Add the custom floating bottom navbar -->
    <Navbar />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: white;
  }

  h1 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #f0f0f0;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .content-section h3 {
    color: #d4af37;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content-section h4 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .highlight {
    background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.1);
    border-left: 4px solid #d4af37;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .viz-showcase {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .viz-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #8b7355;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .viz-demo {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .interaction-principles {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .principle-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #8b7355;
  }

  .navigation-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .nav-buttons {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .button {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .button.is-light {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    color: #f0f0f0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-light:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-primary {
    background: #8b7355;
    color: white;
    border: 1px solid #8b7355;
  }

  .button.is-primary:hover {
    background: #a0845f;
  }

  /* Add padding to body to prevent navbar overlap */
  body {
    padding-bottom: 100px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .nav-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
    
    .container {
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .viz-showcase {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
